{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-challenges-fill-in-the-blank-show-tsx","path":"/learn/a2-english-for-developers/learn-how-to-discuss-roles-and-responsibilities/task-89","result":{"data":{"challengeNode":{"challenge":{"title":"Vežba 89","description":"<section id=\"description\">\n<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">Work overtime</span> to znači raditi više sati od uobičajenog radnog rasporeda. Na primer, <span class=\"highlighted-text\">I usually work overtime during project deadlines</span> to znači raditi dodatni posao kako bi se ispune rokovi projekta.</p>\n<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">Unless</span> Koristi se za razgovor o izuzeku nečega ili uspostavljanje uslova koji onemogućavaju da prethodno izjava bude istinita. To znači <span class=\"highlighted-text\">if it's not the case</span>. Na primer, <span class=\"highlighted-text\">I walk to work unless it rains</span> znači da ću ići na posao ako ne padne kiša.</p>\n<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">Urgent</span> znači nešto što je veoma važno i mora biti odmah uzeto u obzir. Na primer, <span class=\"highlighted-text\">The project is urgent</span> znači da se projekat hitno mora završiti.</p>\n<p>U negativnoj rečenici, <span class=\"highlighted-text\">don't/doesn't have to</span> pokazuje da nešto nije potrebno. Na primer, <span class=\"highlighted-text\">I don't have to work late</span> znači da raditi noću nije obavezno.</p>\n</section>","instructions":"","explanation":null,"challengeType":22,"helpCategory":"English","superBlock":"a2-english-for-developers","block":"learn-how-to-discuss-roles-and-responsibilities","lang":"en-US","fields":{"slug":"/learn/a2-english-for-developers/learn-how-to-discuss-roles-and-responsibilities/task-89"},"fillInTheBlank":{"sentence":"<p>Well, I have to attend team meetings and provide progress reports, but I don't have to work BLANK BLANK it's an BLANK situation.</p>","blanks":[{"answer":"overtime","feedback":"<p>Radi se o radu više sati od onih koji su obično zakazani.</p>"},{"answer":"unless","feedback":"<p>Uvodi uslov koji poništava prethodnu izjavu.</p>"},{"answer":"urgent","feedback":"<p>To znači da je potrebno preduzeti akciju ili obratiti hitnu pažnju.</p>"}]},"inputType":null,"tests":[],"transcript":null,"scene":{"setup":{"background":"company2-boardroom.png","characters":[{"character":"Bob","position":{"x":50,"y":15,"z":1.2},"opacity":0}],"audio":{"filename":"3.3-4.mp3","startTime":1,"startTimestamp":17.38,"finishTimestamp":24.62},"alwaysShowDialogue":null},"commands":[{"background":null,"character":"Bob","position":null,"opacity":1,"startTime":0,"finishTime":null,"dialogue":null},{"background":null,"character":"Bob","position":null,"opacity":null,"startTime":1,"finishTime":4.58,"dialogue":{"text":"Well, I have to attend team meetings and provide progress reports,","align":"center"}},{"background":null,"character":"Bob","position":null,"opacity":null,"startTime":4.7,"finishTime":8.24,"dialogue":{"text":"but I don't have to work over time unless it's an urgent situation.","align":"center"}},{"background":null,"character":"Bob","position":null,"opacity":0,"startTime":8.74,"finishTime":null,"dialogue":null}]},"translationPending":false}}},"pageContext":{"challengeMeta":{"blockHashSlug":"/learn/a2-english-for-developers/#learn-how-to-discuss-roles-and-responsibilities","dashedName":"task-89","certification":"a2-english-for-developers","disableLoopProtectTests":false,"disableLoopProtectPreview":false,"superBlock":"a2-english-for-developers","chapter":null,"module":null,"block":"learn-how-to-discuss-roles-and-responsibilities","isFirstStep":false,"template":null,"required":[],"isLastChallengeInBlock":false,"nextChallengePath":"/learn/a2-english-for-developers/learn-how-to-discuss-roles-and-responsibilities/task-90","prevChallengePath":"/learn/a2-english-for-developers/learn-how-to-discuss-roles-and-responsibilities/task-88","id":"65d959d3478ceb77dc1b28a3","saveSubmissionToDB":null},"projectPreview":{"challengeDat